n532: \n533: ---\n534: \n535: ### Task 20: Create test configuration and CI setup\n536: - [ ] Create `integrations/dify-plugin/setup.py` or `pyproject.toml`\n537: - [ ] Configure test dependencies (pytest, pytest-cov, pytest-mock)\n538: - [ ] Create pytest configuration (`pytest.ini` or `pyproject.toml`)\n539: - [ ] Configure test discovery patterns\n540: - [ ] Configure coverage reporting\n541: - [ ] Add GitHub Actions workflow for testing (if applicable)\n542: - [ ] Run full test suite\n543: - [ ] Generate coverage report\n544: \n545: **Verification**:\n546: ```bash\n547: cd integrations/dify-plugin && python -m pytest --cov=. --cov-report=html && echo \"Tests with coverage pass\" || echo \"Tests fail\"\n548: cd integrations/dify-plugin && coverage report | grep \"TOTAL\" && echo \"Coverage generated\" || echo \"Coverage not generated\"\n549: ```\n550: \n551: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n552: - Test configuration is complete\n553: - All tests pass\n554: - Coverage report is generated\n555: - Coverage meets 80% threshold\n556: \n557: ---\n558: \n559: ### Task 21: Test plugin package installation\n560: - [ ] Build plugin package\n561: - [ ] Test package installation in clean environment\n562: - [ ] Verify all dependencies are installed\n563: - [ ] Test plugin import\n564: - [ ] Test main.py execution\n565: - [ ] Test provider import\n566: - [ ] Test tool import\n567: - [ ] Verify no import errors\n568: \n569: **Verification**:\n570: ```bash\n571: cd integrations/dify-plugin && python -c \"from dify_plugin import Plugin; from provider.agentcube import AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider; from tools.agentcube_code_interpreter import AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool\" && echo \"All imports work\" || echo \"Import errors found\"\n572: ```\n573: \n574: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n575: - Package installs without errors\n576: - All modules import correctly\n577: - No dependency conflicts\n578: - Plugin can be loaded\n579: \n580: ---\n581: \n582: ### Task 22: Test plugin with Dify platform (mock or real)\n583: - [ ] Set up test Dify instance (mock or real)\n584: - [ ] Install plugin in Dify\n585: - [ ] Verify plugin appears in plugin list\n586: - [ ] Configure tool in Dify UI\n587: - [ ] Test tool invocation with code\n588: - [ ] Test tool invocation with command\n589: - [ ] Test credential validation\n590: - [ ] Test error scenarios\n591: - [ ] Verify JSON response format\n592: - [ ] Test timeout handling\n593: \n594: **Verification**:\n595: ```bash\n596: # Manual verification or automated tests with Dify API\n597: ```\n598: \n599: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n600: - Plugin installs and loads in Dify\n601: - Tool can be configured\n602: - Tool invocations work correctly\n603: - Errors are handled properly\n604: - Responses match expected format\n605: \n606: ---\n607: \n608: ### Task 23: Performance testing\n609: - [ ] Measure plugin startup time\n610: - [ ] Measure tool invocation latency\n611: - [ ] Test with concurrent invocations\n612: - [ ] Measure memory usage\n613: - [ ] Test with large code blocks\n614: - [ ] Test with long-running commands\n615: - [ ] Identify performance bottlenecks\n616: - [ ] Optimize if necessary\n617: - [ ] Document performance characteristics\n618: \n619: **Verification**:\n620: ```bash\n621: cd integrations/dify-plugin && python -m pytest tests/test_performance.py -v && echo \"Performance tests pass\" || echo \"Performance tests fail\"\n622: ```\n623: \n624: **Acceptance Criteria**:\n625: - Plugin starts within acceptable time\n626: - Tool invocations complete within acceptable time\n627: - Memory usage is reasonable\n628: - No memory leaks detected\n629: - Performance is documented\n630: \n631: ---\n632: \n633: ### Task 24: Security testing\n634: - [ ] Test with malicious code inputs\n635: - [ ] Test with injection attacks\n636: - [ ] Test with excessively large inputs\n637: - [ ] Verify secrets are not logged\n638: - [ ] Test with invalid credentials\n639: - [ ] Verify proper error messages (no information leakage)