ptable\n745: - Plugin can be packaged and distributed\n746: \n747: ### Dependencies\n748: - Python 3.12+\n749: - dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n750: - agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n751: - Dify platform for testing (or mock environment)\n752: - Existing integrations module structure\n753: - Code interpreter API endpoints (router_url, workload_manager_url)\n754: \n755: ### Blocked By\n756: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n757: \n758: ### Blocks\n759: - None currently identified\n760: \n761: ### Notes\n762: - Follow Dify plugin conventions exactly as specified in design\n763: - All YAML files must match exact structure from design.md\n764: - Tool parameters must match exact schema from spec.md\n765: - Plugin should be optional and configurable\n766: - Ensure proper error handling for production use\n767: - Add comprehensive logging for debugging\n768: - Maintain backward compatibility with Dify plugin framework\n769: - Test thoroughly with real Dify instance if possible\n770: - Document any deviations from design\n771: - Keep plugin package lightweight and focused\n772: - Follow security best practices\n773: - Ensure type safety with mypy\n774: - Maintain code quality with linting tools\n775: - All tests should be fast and reliable\n776: - Plugin should handle errors gracefully\n777: - Performance should be acceptable for production use\n778: - Memory usage should be reasonable\n779: - Plugin should not leak resources\n780: - Documentation should be kept in sync with code\n781: - Examples should be updated when code changes\n782: - Version numbers should follow semantic versioning\n783: - Dependencies should be kept up to date\n784: - Security vulnerabilities should be addressed promptly\n785: - Plugin should be tested on multiple Python versions if supported\n786: - Plugin should be tested on multiple platforms if supported\n\n(End of file - total 786 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036 — Dify 插件集成 Tasks\n\n**Module**: `integrations`\n**Language**: Python\n*